A Grade11 Forest High pupil appeared in the Johannesburg magistrate's court on Wednesday. JOHANNESBURG - A Grade11 Forest High pupil is expected to apply for bail on Thursday. He appeared in the Johannesburg magistrate's court on Wednesday morning after being arrested for the fatal stabbing of another pupil. It's alleged he stabbed to death a fellow pupil outside Forest High School in Johannesburg. READ: Pupil arrested for fatal stabbing Two other pupils aged 15 and 18 were also wounded. The National Prosecuting Authority has indicated it will not oppose bail. Mid-year exams at the school have been suspended for now.